<section id="slide-orge8bb820" data-background="./sos.png" data-background-size="100px" data-background-position="1% 96%" data-background-opacity="0.4">
<h2 id="orge8bb820">Where did our campus' Open Source culture go?</h2>
<p>
As you might have noticed, Linux adoption is very low on campus among students and faculty alike!
As a premier Technological Institute, we should have a much, much higher rate of Linux adoption.
</p>
</section>
</section>
<section>
<section id="slide-orgb6ab344" data-background="./sos.png" data-background-size="100px" data-background-position="1% 96%" data-background-opacity="0.4">
<h2 id="orgb6ab344">Why do we need it?</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-orgb6ab344">
</div>
</section>
<section id="slide-orge1dc7b3" data-background="./sos.png" data-background-size="100px" data-background-position="1% 96%" data-background-opacity="0.4">
<h3 id="orge1dc7b3">GNU/Linux provides a better environment for programming.</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-orge1dc7b3">
</div>
</section>
<section id="slide-orge45493a" data-background="./sos.png" data-background-size="100px" data-background-position="1% 96%" data-background-opacity="0.4">
<h4 id="orge45493a">Windows PATHs are a nightmare to set and manage</h4>
<p>
To set up programming-related software, users often have to modify Window's PATH. This is widely agreed to be notoriously difficult, not to mention time-consuming. Package managers automatically set PATH variables when required on Linux, and it is much easier to do so manually when the need arises.
</p>
</section>
<section id="slide-orgae46037" data-background="./sos.png" data-background-size="100px" data-background-position="1% 96%" data-background-opacity="0.4">
<h4 id="orgae46037">Windows has no package manager</h4>
<p>
Package managers are very useful for getting free software with one click. This includes applications such as VLC, Blender, Audacity etc. and programming software such as Python, GCC, Clang etc.
</p>
</section>
<section id="slide-orge97e3d1" data-background="./sos.png" data-background-size="100px" data-background-position="1% 96%" data-background-opacity="0.4">
